President Muhammadu Buhari Friday said he had directed the resuscitation of the Ajaokuta Steel Plant. In a national broadcast to mark 2020 Democracy day, the President said this was in line with his administration’s commitment to expanding the mining sector. “We remain committed to expanding our mining sector. To this end, I have directed the resuscitation of the Ajaokuta Steel Plant based on Government-to-Government financing and a Public-Private Sector financing,” the president said. Buhari said with foreign and domestic investments and the participation of Small Scale Miners, his government was harnessing the supply value chain in gold production. Details later…